Program: Outlook
Title: 29/10/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00bj0kj
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 1 Nov 2010
Bollywood star Preity Zinta tells us what it's like to own troubled Indian cricket team Kings XI Punjab. She also reveals how she felt when she stood up to Mumbai's mafia in court, despite receiving threats and how she narrowly escaped death twice in two weeks. The actress describes to Aasmah Mir the personal impact of surviving a bomb attack in Sri Lanka and the Tsunami in Thailand why these events made her want to give something back to society. Show less